article.headline: North Carolina A&T 80, Norfolk St. 60
article.story: GREENSBORO, N.C. (AP) -- Greg Roberts scored 24 points to lead four players in double-digit scoring and lift North Carolina A&T past Norfolk State 80-60 on Saturday. Steven Rush came off the bench to score 15 points, Austin Ewing added 12, and Angelo Hernandez posted 11 for the Aggies (9-11, 5-3 Mid-Eastern Athletic Conference), who shot 74.2 percent (23-for-31) from the foul line. Tony Murphy scored 22 points, Brandon Plummer came off the bench to add 16, and Tynell Dunkley finished with 11 points and eight rebounds for the Spartans (5-13, 5-3), who shot just 37.5 percent from the field. Calvin Brown had nine rebounds and nine points. The Aggies led 35-32 at the half.
